 fs7 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">tithe during Christ&apos;s priesthood? </div><div class="t m65e x59 h2b y14c7 ff4 fs10 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">DURING THE LEVITICAL PRIESTHOOD </div><div class="t m1cd x4a h27 y1d74 ff4 fs7 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">5. </div><div class="t m102 x29 h27 y12a6 ff4 fs7 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">What shows that Jacob, Abraham&apos;s grandson, un-</div><div class="t mdd1 xe h27 y13b2 ff4 fs7 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">derstood perfectly his obligation to God regarding the </div><div class="t ma06 x4 h27 y108d ff4 fs7 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">payment of tithe? Gen. 28 : 20-22. Note 2. </div><div class="t m1d0 x4a h27 y1057 ff4 fs7 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">6. </div><div class="t m33d x29 h27 y1dac ff4 fs7 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">About twenty years later, when he came back to </div><div class="t ma34 xe h27 y118a ff4 fs7 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">his old home in safety, what substantial evidence could </div><div class="t m52f xe h27 y13c6 ff4 fs7 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">Jacob (now Israel) present of the Lord&apos;s prospering </div><div class="t mab x4 h27 yeaf ff4 fs7 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">care over him? Gen. 32 : 13-18; 33: 8-11. (See margin, </div><div class="t m1ce x4 h27 y11e7 ff4 fs7 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">verse 11.) </div><div class="t m1d2 x4a h27 y1545 ff4 fs7 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">7. </div><div class="t m450 x29 h27 y1391 ff4 fs7 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">What commandment did God give to the children </div><div class="t m26d x4 h27 yc84 ff4 fs7 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">of Israel concerning the tithe? Lev. 27 : 30-34. </div><div class="t m1d5 x18 h27 yeb3 ff4 fs7 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">8. </div><div class="t m443 x29 h27 y1eb4 ff4 fs7 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">On one occasion what were the Levites compelled </div><div class="t m96 x4 h27 y1557 ff4 fs7 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">to do, when through selfishness the other tribes of Israel </div><div class="t m900 x4 h27 y1608 ff4 fs7 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">withheld the tithe? Neh. 13: 10. </div><div class="t m6fa x18 h27 y1c3e ff4 fs7 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">9, Uow was this condition corrected,? Verses 11</div><div class="t m309e xa9 h27 y